Since this thread is just starting. I want to ask you guys for some lesser known stories that you would like recommend. What are your favorite moments form said story?
I'll start with my favorite one so far:
Spent casings by zhidkovv (https://archiveofourown.org/works/53344993/chapters/135008455)

I really like this story because is a really nice subversion of your typical Anthrostate story (this one takes place in liveiron's Negligent Discharge universe). This time the human has the upper hand and manages to capture an Anthro that is a complete zealot that believes in the state. The main goal of the human is to de-radicalize her by using some unorthodox techniques and some therapy. He makes her see how corrupt the system is and the damage that does to the citizens (them included). It also delves a little bit into the conflict that created this world and how unfair it was to fight against the anthros that invaded and eventually took over the earth.

I would say that this is the story I wish Shelby's story was, because in that story when the titular Shelby encounters the blatant corruption in the government that she idolizes it doesn't affect her in the slightest. She never questions anything and continues like nothing happened. While in Spent casings when the main anthro is shown the corruption and manipulation of the state that completely shatters her reality and causes her to have a mental breakdown that start her de-radicalization.
I highly recommend this story, it still is unfinished but the author updates semi-regularly.
